Usage: verifyMetalDensity [-help] [-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}] [-detailed]
                          [-ignoreLEFDensity] [-oversize <integer>]
                          [-report <string>] [-layer <string>]

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}           # Specifies the coordinates of the area to verify
                              # (box, optional)
-detailed                     # Generates a detailed metal density report
                              # (bool, optional)
-ignoreLEFDensity             # Ignore MACRO density table in LEF file
                              # (bool, optional)
-layer <string>               # Specifies the LEF or Encounter layers to verify
                              # (string, optional)
-oversize <integer>           # Specifies an offset value for the area to
                              # verify (int, optional)
-report <string>              # Specifies the report file for the metal density
                              # violation information (string, optional)